= Early Pregnancy Complications

== Abortion

=== Habitual Abortion
*Definition* #viva
- ≥3 consecutive spontaneous abortions before 20 weeks.

#high_yeild
- *Causes:*
  - Uterine anomalies (especially septate uterus)
  - Antiphospholipid antibody syndrome (APLA)
  - Parental balanced chromosomal translocation
  - Luteal phase defect
  - Poorly controlled diabetes, thyroid disorders
- *Investigations:*
  - Parental karyotyping
  - Antiphospholipid antibody testing
  - Uterine evaluation (HSG/sonohysterography)

---

=== Threatened Abortion
*Definition* #viva
- Bleeding before 20 weeks with closed cervical os and live fetus.

==== Management
#viva
- Bed rest and reassurance
- Avoid intercourse
- Progesterone supplementation if indicated
- Treat infections
- Rh-D Ig 50 mcg IM if Rh negative

#high_yeild
- *Prognosis:* Presence of fetal cardiac activity on USG — best indicator of continuation.
- *Anti-D:* Administer 50 mcg if Rh negative.

---

=== Missed Abortion
*Definition* #viva
- Fetal death before 20 weeks with retention of products in uterus.

==== Complications
#viva
- Infection
- DIC (if retained >4 weeks)
- Subinvolution

#high_yeild
- *USG Criteria:*
  - CRL >7 mm with no cardiac activity
  - MSD >25 mm with no embryo
- *Coagulation:* Prolonged retention → release of thromboplastin → DIC risk.

