=== Septic Abortion
*Definition* #viva
- Infection involving uterus and/or pelvic tissues following abortion.

==== Complications
#viva
- Endometritis
- Pelvic abscess
- Peritonitis
- Septicemia
- DIC
- Renal failure

==== Management
#viva
- *Case:* 9 weeks pregnancy, induced abortion, fever, foul discharge.
  - *Provisional Diagnosis:* Septic abortion.
  - *Confirmation:* Clinical findings + USG pelvis + culture of discharge/blood.
  - *Principles of management:*
    - Hospitalization and monitoring
    - IV fluids and broad-spectrum antibiotics (cephalosporin + metronidazole + gentamicin)
    - Uterine evacuation after stabilization
    - Manage complications (DIC, renal failure)

#high_yeild
- *Organism:* _Clostridium perfringens_ (gas gangrene) — rare, fatal.
- *Grades:*
  - I – Infection limited to uterus
  - II – Involves adnexa/pelvis
  - III – Generalized peritonitis or sepsis

