== Menstrual Regulation (MR)
*Definition* #viva
- Evacuation of uterine contents within 14 days of missed period, without confirming pregnancy.

=== Complications
#viva
- Incomplete evacuation
- Hemorrhage
- Infection/sepsis
- Uterine perforation

- *Case:* 25yo, 3 days post-MR, pain, bleeding, foul discharge.
  - *Diagnosis:* Incomplete septic abortion.
  - *Investigations:*
    - USG pelvis
    - CBC
    - Serum β-hCG
    - Culture/sensitivity
  - *Management:*
    - IV fluids and antibiotics
    - Uterine evacuation under antibiotic cover
    - Rh prophylaxis if indicated

