== Ectopic Pregnancy
*Definition* #viva
- Implantation of fertilized ovum outside uterine cavity.

=== Sites
#viva
- Fallopian tube (most common)
  - Ampulla (70%)
  - Isthmus
  - Fimbria
- Interstitial (cornual)
- Ovarian
- Cervical
- Abdominal

#high_yeild
- *Ampulla:* Most common site.
- *Interstitial/Cornual:* Most dangerous — delayed rupture, severe hemorrhage.

=== Risk Factors
#viva
- PID
- Previous ectopic pregnancy
- Tubal surgery or ligation
- IUCD use
- ART/IVF conception
- Endometriosis
- Tubal anomalies

=== Diagnosis
#viva
- *Investigations:*
  - Urine/serum β-hCG
  - Transvaginal USG
  - Diagnostic laparoscopy (if uncertain)
- *Case:* Short amenorrhea, lancinating pain, shock (Pulse 120, BP 80/40)
  - *Provisional Diagnosis:* Ruptured ectopic pregnancy
  - *Investigations:*
    - USG/FAST
    - β-hCG
    - Hb, blood grouping & cross-matching

#high_yeild
- *β-hCG Doubling Time:* Rise < 66% in 48 hr — suggests nonviable/ectopic pregnancy.
- *Classic Triad:* Amenorrhea, abdominal pain, vaginal bleeding (seen in < 50% cases).

=== Management
#viva
- *Medical:*
  - Methotrexate — single/multidose regimens
- *Surgical:*
  - Salpingostomy
  - Salpingectomy
  - Laparoscopy/laparotomy based on stability

#high_yeild
- *Methotrexate Criteria:*
  - Hemodynamically stable
  - Sac < 3.5 cm
  - No fetal cardiac activity
  - β-hCG < 5000 IU/L

