== Gestational Trophoblastic Disease (GTD)

=== Hydatidiform Mole
*Definition* #viva
- Cystic swelling of chorionic villi with trophoblastic proliferation.

==== Diagnosis
#viva
- *Clinical Features:*
  - Amenorrhea followed by irregular bleeding
  - Uterus larger than expected
  - Early-onset pre-eclampsia
  - Hyperemesis
- *Investigations:*
  - USG — “snowstorm” / “cluster of grapes”
  - β-hCG markedly elevated
  - Theca lutein cysts (bilateral)

- *Case:* 12 weeks amenorrhea, severe vomiting, uterus > dates, “snow storm” USG.
  - *Provisional Diagnosis:* Complete hydatidiform mole.

#high_yeild
- *Complete Mole:*
  - 46XX, paternal origin (empty ovum fertilized by sperm)
  - No fetus
  - Higher malignancy rate
- *Partial Mole:*
  - 69XXY triploidy
  - Fetus may be present
- *Ovaries:* Bilateral theca lutein cysts due to high hCG.

==== Management
===== Management of the case
#viva
- Evacuation by suction under oxytocin cover.
- Histopathological confirmation.
- Anti-D to Rh-negative women.
- Baseline chest X-ray, LFTs, renal function.

===== Follow-up regime
#viva
- β-hCG weekly until normal ×3 weeks.
- Then monthly ×6 months.
- Chest X-ray if rising levels.

===== Contraception during follow-up
#viva
- Avoid conception for at least 6–12 months.
- Use barrier or combined OCPs.

==== Complications
#viva
- Persistent GTN
- Choriocarcinoma
- Uterine perforation
- Embolization

