=== Gestational Trophoblastic Neoplasia (GTN)
*Definition* #viva
- Persistent or malignant trophoblastic proliferation with elevated β-hCG after any pregnancy.

==== Classification
#viva
- Invasive mole
- Choriocarcinoma
- Placental site trophoblastic tumor (PSTT)
- Epithelioid trophoblastic tumor (ETT)

==== Chemotherapy
===== Indications following mole evacuation
#viva
- Rising or plateaued β-hCG
- Metastatic disease
- Histologic diagnosis of malignancy
- Very high initial β-hCG (>20,000 IU/L)

#high_yeild
- *Choriocarcinoma:* Early hematogenous spread — primarily to lungs and vagina.
- *Scoring:* WHO prognostic scoring:
  - ≤6 → Low risk → Methotrexate
  - >6 → High risk → EMA-CO regimen